main event: Several unidentified flying objects were observed over Dallas, Texas, at high speeds and irregular angles.
interesting points: Objects were seen at intervals over about an hour,Objects showed different sizes and colors, and reflected sunlight with a metallic sheen,No sound was reported from the objects, The sighting was concluded to be astronomical due to daylight brightness, The object was moving at an estimated speed of over 600 mph.
witness description: One witness was a private pilot with considerable experience in observing aircraft. He stated that the object was not a conventional aircraft.
